&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Development Opportunity &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interested in developing our quality agenda further? Are you enthusiastic? Self motivated? Up for a challenge?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the answer is yes then this is an opportunity to be part of our Quality improvement and compliance team. We are looking for an innovative person who will support the development of quality improvement and ensure the CHCP meets its quality agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will work closely with corporate, operational and clinical colleagues, to ensure that standards are embedded into practice &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to demonstrate excellent communication skills including report writing, have knowledge of a range of skills in auditing, be confident in managing change and be able to work effectively with clinicians and service users. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a dynamic and enthusiastic individual to join our Quality improvement and compliance team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition this is a development role whereby following a period of training objectives the role will be substantive at band 5.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Contact details:&lt;br /&gt; Claire Attwood, I&lt;span&gt;nformation Governance &amp; Compliance Manager &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Tel: 07525873558 | &lt;span&gt;Email claire.attwood@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
